1
00:00:05,300 --> 00:00:11,500
Prahlād Mahārāj survives
the attacks of Hiraṇyakaśipu,

2
00:00:11,500 --> 00:00:14,470
and this leads
Hiraṇyakaśipu to wonder

3
00:00:14,470 --> 00:00:20,320
about the extraordinary power 
of Prahlād Mahārāj,

4
00:00:20,320 --> 00:00:21,800
and to enquire from him,

5
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:26,220
[Where Is God Located?]

6
00:00:26,300 --> 00:00:30,620
“Prahlād, where did
you get this power?”

7
00:00:30,900 --> 00:00:32,470
And Prahlād’s answer is,

8
00:00:32,470 --> 00:00:37,750
“From the Original Source of all power.
Where did you get your power?

9
00:00:38,500 --> 00:00:44,500
Where you’re getting your power,
I’m getting mine.”

10
00:00:47,500 --> 00:00:50,500
It’s like the Dylan Thomas 
line about,

11
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:53,300
“Does not …”,
what is it …

12
00:00:53,300 --> 00:00:57,500
“That force that drives the fuse
in the green flower,

13
00:00:57,500 --> 00:01:00,500
drives my … drives me.”

14
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:05,400
So that’s a Brahman-type description,
but he is taking it deeper.

15
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:07,400
And really 
it’s the same source.

16
00:01:07,400 --> 00:01:11,190
“Where you get your power?
That’s where I get my power.”

17
00:01:11,700 --> 00:01:14,500
And Hiraṇyakaśipu, 
we hear he is saying,

18
00:01:14,500 --> 00:01:21,600
“Oh, this God of yours,
where is he located?”

19
00:01:21,600 --> 00:01:25,290
Prahlād Mahārāj,
“He’s everywhere.”

20
00:01:27,100 --> 00:01:30,530
When one of Guru Mahārāj’s relatives
saw him becoming too …

21
00:01:30,530 --> 00:01:34,700
we’re talking 
about relative obstruction,

22
00:01:34,700 --> 00:01:39,000
as one of his uncles saw 
he is too much inclined
 

23
00:01:39,000 --> 00:01:42,000
towards Kṛṣṇa consciousness
and renunciation,

24
00:01:42,000 --> 00:01:46,900
he thought to put a damper 
on his theistic sentiments and he said,

25
00:01:46,900 --> 00:01:48,900
“You know … 
do you know,

26
00:01:48,900 --> 00:01:51,900
there are some stars, 
we hear from science, there are …

27
00:01:51,900 --> 00:01:56,150
They’re so far away, their light 
has yet to reach the Earth.

28
00:01:56,700 --> 00:01:58,800
So if there is a God,

29
00:01:58,800 --> 00:02:00,570
we are so insignificant again,
do you think

30
00:02:00,570 --> 00:02:05,260
He has any time 
for people like us?”

31
00:02:07,300 --> 00:02:13,000
And Guru Mahārāj’s response to him
was to recall the Upaniṣads, Īśopaniṣad,

32
00:02:13,000 --> 00:02:17,500
tad ejati tan naijati
tad dūre tad v antike

33
00:02:17,500 --> 00:02:22,800
tad antar asya sarvasya
tad u sarvasyāsya bāhyataḥ.

34
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:25,400
He’s saying, “Yes, He is
very far away, but it says,

35
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:29,200
‘He is also
nearest and dearest.’

36
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:33,560
Is there anywhere
where God is not?”

37
00:02:34,600 --> 00:02:38,700
aṇḍāntara-stha-paramāṇu-cayāntara-stham
[Bs: 5.35]

38
00:02:38,700 --> 00:02:41,900
So his uncle was
[sound “hmmghh”] …

39
00:02:41,900 --> 00:02:45,900
was … frustrated.

40
00:02:47,900 --> 00:02:49,530
Whereas Guru Mahārāj
would sometimes say,

41
00:02:49,530 --> 00:02:51,600
these arguments— 
how do they end,

42
00:02:51,600 --> 00:02:54,100
“That man was silenced!”
[Laughing]

43
00:02:54,100 --> 00:02:57,500
He said, “Is there
anywhere where God is not?”

44
00:02:57,500 --> 00:02:59,500
Whereas Bengalis
tell Prabhupād,

45
00:02:59,500 --> 00:03:05,100
“Swamiji, why we must go to the temple
to worship, if God is everywhere?”

46
00:03:05,100 --> 00:03:08,400
Prabhupād said,
“So He is not in temple?!”

47
00:03:08,400 --> 00:03:12,990
He is everywhere except
the temple! That’s interesting—

48
00:03:13,000 --> 00:03:15,480
God is everywhere, 
but not in the temple.

49
00:03:15,480 --> 00:03:17,160
[Laughing]

